Task: Ratatui and crossterm Enter + key modifier behavior

 <p>I'm trying to write a text input for a chat app using ratatui and crossterm. And I want to have an intuitive way of inputting new lines since enter is reserved for sending.</p>
<p>This is what I came up with:</p>
<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>KeyCode::Enter if key.modifiers.contains(KeyModifiers::ALT) &amp;&amp; $vim_mode == Vim::Insert =&gt; { // NOTE: Specific to this app, allows new lines in messages
    $input.insert($cursor_pos, '\n');
    $cursor_pos += 1;
},
KeyCode::Enter =&gt; { // NOTE: Specific to this app
    if n==0 { n = 1 };
    for _ in 0..n.min(10) {
        if !$input.is_empty() {
            let sender_id = $chat.current_user.get_id();
            let message = Message::new(-1, sender_id, $input.clone());
            $chat.message_history.write().unwrap().push(message);
        }
    }
    $seq.clear();
    $input.clear();
    $cursor_pos = 0;
},
</code></pre>
<p>This snippet works perfectly but I want to be able to use shift enter and ctrl enter for better user experience. The problem is that they don't work out of the box. As far as I tested, they don't even get detected. But, surprisingly, there are tui apps which have them working.</p>
<p>Is there a way to do this in crossterm?</p>


