    |                                         ----------------- borrow of `components_buffer` occurs here
...
398 |                 components_buffer = clear_vector(components_buffer);
    |                                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    |                                                  |
    |                                                  move out of `components_buffer` occurs here
    |                                                  borrow later used here

Some errors have detailed explanations: E0499, E0505.
</code></pre>
<p>If I understand these errors, the borrow checker considers the <code>components_buffer</code> to be borrowed by the <code>callback(...)</code> after it's finished once. <strong>So the most basic question is: how can I tell the borrow checker that <code>components_buffer</code> is borrowed only for the duration of the <code>callback(...)</code>?</strong> The callback isn't supposed to store references to the components anywhere (even for the next execution), it must consider them possibly deallocated after the callback ends. (If it needs to store some data, it needs to copy and use own buffer.)</p>
<p><strong>The alternative question is: is there a better way to achieve this?</strong> Note that the inner loop needs to be as fast as possible.</p>
<p>Various notes about the example:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>The <code>RefCell</code> is there only as a workaround to resolve other borrow checker issues, but it's not strictly necessary. The runtime overhead there is acceptable.</p>
