<p>Potentially, some important precalculations can be done when one wants the difference for many other points. To do so, I wanted to create a method that accepts both, <em>a list of offsets and another list of values to compute the difference for.</em></p>
<p>The operation is not really a difference, and the resulting type is very large. This is why I would like to return the result of this operation as a lazy iterator that calculates the result on the fly. So I can use it in some other method one after the other without having to allocate huge amounts of memory.</p>
<p>This would result in an 3-nested iterator. From outer iterator to inner:</p>
<ol>
<li>iterates over all the offsets</li>
<li>iterates over all the provided values</li>
<li>iterates over all the members of the collection.</li>
</ol>
<p>I am havin trouble with closures lifetimes. And while I somewhat understand the issue, I don't quite know how to solve it.</p>
