Task: Making custom language with Pest crate in rust, rule is not working

 <p>So I made this PEG parser for parsing my custom language:</p>
<pre class="lang-none prettyprint-override"><code>// 1. Root Rule
program = { SOI ~ stmt* ~ EOI }

// 2. Statements
// Use a positive lookahead (&amp;) to check if an '=' exists later in the line
stmt = _{ assignment | func_call | block }

// 3. Assignment
// We look ahead to find an '=' after the identifier/type to &quot;confirm&quot; this is an assignment
assignment = { ident ~ (&quot;:&quot; ~ ident)? ~ &quot;=&quot; ~ expr }

// 4. Function Call
// We use a negative lookahead (!&quot;=&quot;) to ensure we DON'T match if an '=' is coming up.
// This prevents 'a' in 'a = 1' from being seen as a function call.
func_call = { func_head ~ !(&quot;=&quot;) ~ expr* }
func_head = _{ ident | symbol }

// 5. Blocks
block = { &quot;do&quot; ~ stmt* ~ &quot;end&quot; }

// 6. Expressions
// This order is vital. We want to try specific things like numbers/strings 
// before we try the very general 'func_call'.
expr = { 
    &quot;(&quot; ~ expr ~ &quot;)&quot; 
    | block 
    | string 
    | number 
    | func_call 
    | ident 
}

