 <p><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/string/trait.ToString.html" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>ToString</code></a> trait documentation states that &quot;<code>ToString</code> shouldn’t be implemented directly: <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/fmt/trait.Display.html" rel="nofollow noreferrer" title="trait std::fmt::Display"><code>Display</code></a> should be implemented instead&quot;. Even a such fundamental type as <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/primitive.bool.html" rel="nofollow noreferrer">bool</a> seems to follow this rule: eventhough both variants can be represented with a simple <code>&quot;true&quot;</code> or <code>&quot;false&quot;</code> string literal with no <code>Formatter</code> required, it still <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/src/core/fmt/mod.rs.html#2696-2700" rel="nofollow noreferrer">implements</a> <code>Display</code> like everything else:</p>
<pre><code>impl Display for bool {
    fn fmt(&amp;self, f: &amp;mut Formatter&lt;'_&gt;) -&gt; Result {
