<p>So the question is, how do I do something like that myself? I have a custom primitive type (which is a wrapper around another primitive type) that can be represented with a few string literals. It does not need a <code>Formatter</code> to be converted into a string via <code>to_string</code>. However, this <code>SpecToString</code> trait is not public, so I can't go that way. I will implement <code>Display</code> for my type as well, but I just don't like the idea of creating a <code>Formatter</code> when I don't need it. Both documentation and clippy are against implementing <code>ToString</code> manually, and since this type will be a part of public API, I cannot just fiwb it either. What should I do in such situation? Are there other crates that handle this issue?</p>


