Task: How to prevent &quot;appstarting&quot; cursor when calling IContextMenu::QueryContextMenu?

 <p>I'm building a file explorer application and encountering an issue where <code>IContextMenu::QueryContextMenu</code> causes the cursor to briefly flash to the &quot;appstarting&quot; (arrow + spinner) cursor.</p>
<p><strong>This happens in two scenarios:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Normal right-click</strong>: User right-clicks a file, spinner briefly appears while building the context menu</li>
<li><strong>Preloading</strong>: I preload context menu data when the user selects a file (to make right-click instant), and the spinner appears during preload</li>
</ol>
<p>Both cases have the same root cause: <code>QueryContextMenu</code> internally triggers shell extensions that call <code>SetCursor(appstarting)</code>.</p>
<h3>What I've tried:</h3>
<div class="s-table-container"><table class="s-table">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Approach</th>
<th>Result</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>SetCursor(IDC_ARROW)</code> immediately after <code>QueryContextMenu</code></td>
<td>Still flickers - cursor change happens during the call</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Handling <code>WM_SETCURSOR</code> in window proc, always return <code>LRESULT(1)</code></td>
<td>Still flickers - <code>SetCursor</code> is called synchronously, not via messages</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Timer-based shell work instead of <code>PostMessage</code></td>
<td>Still flickers</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>PeekMessage</code> to pump <code>WM_SETCURSOR</code> after shell call</td>
<td>Still flickers</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Debouncing preload (100ms after selection)</td>
<td>Reduces frequency but cursor still appears</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>PostMessage(WM_NULL)</code> + <code>GetMessage</code> trick (from SO thread about <code>WaitForSingleObject</code>)</td>
<td>No effect</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>SetClassLongPtrW(GCLP_HCURSOR)</code> to force class cursor</td>
<td>No effect - <code>SetCursor</code> overrides class cursor</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Using <code>TrackPopupMenu</code> immediately after <code>QueryContextMenu</code></td>
<td>Still flickers - spinner appears during <code>QueryContextMenu</code>, not after</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong><code>ShowCursor(FALSE)</code> before, <code>ShowCursor(TRUE)</code> after</strong></td>
<td><strong>WORKS</strong> - but cursor disappears briefly</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<h3>The problem:</h3>
<p>The cursor changes to &quot;appstarting&quot; <strong>during</strong> the <code>QueryContextMenu</code> call. Even if I reset the cursor immediately after, the visual effect is already visible.</p>
<h3>Minimal repro code (Rust with windows crate, but C++ equivalent would be the same):</h3>
<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>use windows::Win32::Foundation::*;
