Task: rdkafka::message::ToBytes is not implemented for `&amp;str`

 <p>I am trying to write a Rust program which generates random FX data and sends it to a Kafka topic.</p>
<p>The code I have written so far is quite short. It does not currently compile.</p>
<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>use rdkafka;
use rand;
use rand::seq::IndexedRandom;

fn main() {
    let mut config = rdkafka::config::ClientConfig::new();
    config.set(&quot;bootstrap.servers&quot;, &quot;server:9092&quot;);

    let producer = config.create::&lt;rdkafka::producer::BaseProducer&gt;().unwrap();

    let fx_G10 = [&quot;EURUSD&quot;, &quot;GBPUSD&quot;, &quot;USDJPY&quot;, &quot;AUDCAD&quot;, &quot;AUDUSD&quot;, &quot;USDCAD&quot;, &quot;EURJPY&quot;];

    let mut rng = rand::rng();

    loop {
        let fx = fx_G10.choose(&amp;mut rng).unwrap();

        let payload = &quot;example&quot;;

        let mut message = rdkafka::producer::BaseRecord::to(&quot;example&quot;)
            .payload(payload)
            .key(fx);

        producer.send(message).unwrap();
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>The full error message is</p>
<pre><code>the trait bound `&amp;str: rdkafka::message::ToBytes` is not satisfied
the trait `rdkafka::message::ToBytes` is implemented for `str`
required for `&amp;str` to implement `rdkafka::message::ToBytes`
base_producer.rs(132, 13): required by a bound in `BaseRecord::&lt;'a, K, P, D&gt;::payload`
</code></pre>
<p>My question is <strong>not</strong> <em>&quot;how do I fix this&quot;</em>. I can figure out a way to make this compile, that is not a difficult problem.</p>
<p>What I do not understand is why this code doesn't currently compile.</p>
<p>The elements of <code>fx_G10</code> are <code>&amp;'static str</code>. The size of each element of <code>fx_G10</code> is known at compile time. The length of each element is the same, however obviously that need not necessarily be the case in general. One of these elements could have different length.</p>
<p>Therefore, all we can know about <code>fx_G10</code> at compile time is that it contains references to <code>str</code> (<code>&amp;str</code>) objects, but the sizes of these things might be different.</p>
<p><code>rdkafka::message::ToBytes</code> is implemented for <code>str</code>, <code>String</code> and some other types. (See: <a href="https://docs.rs/rdkafka/latest/rdkafka/message/trait.ToBytes.html" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://docs.rs/rdkafka/latest/rdkafka/message/trait.ToBytes.html</a>)</p>
<p><code>String</code>s are dynamically sized. In other words, their size is not known until runtime. Therefore, whatever <code>rdkafka::message::ToBytes</code> does internally, it must be able to cope with references to data which has a size which is dynamic (not known until runtime).</p>
<p>So why <strong>isn't it implemented for <code>&amp;str</code>?</strong></p>


