<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>use std::marker::PhantomData;

pub struct Foo&lt;'scope, 'env: 'scope&gt; {
    // Marker types matching std::thread::Scope.
    scope: PhantomData&lt;&amp;'scope mut &amp;'scope ()&gt;,
    env: PhantomData&lt;&amp;'env mut &amp;'env ()&gt;,
}

pub fn with_foo&lt;'env, F&gt;(f: F)
where
    F: for&lt;'scope&gt; FnOnce(&amp;'scope Foo&lt;'scope, 'env&gt;),
{
    // Create a Foo struct.
    let foo = Foo {
        scope: PhantomData,
        env: PhantomData,
    };

    // Hand a reference to the function. Only a shared reference; the function
    // shouldn't be allowed to move from `foo`.
    f(&amp;foo);

    // Now that the function has returned it is safe to destroy the Foo by
    // letting it fall out of scope.
}
</code></pre>
<p>However if we define <code>Drop</code> for <code>Foo</code>, it no longer compiles (<a href="https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2021&amp;gist=6866220b7dda16bad4140d1f2d31ca33" rel="nofollow noreferrer">playground</a>):</p>
