<p>Individually, the <code>insert</code> and <code>remove</code> operations are much much faster but when applied together, there is a massive decrease in performance for the noophasher. I tried running <code>perf stat</code> but I got similar results for both. The cargo flamegraph chart was dominated by divan function calls, and I could not see any differences. Since the HashMap is pre-allocated, I don't see that as a possible issue either. I tried looking at the compiler explorer, but I could not discern anything: <a href="https://godbolt.org/z/3nWern4z4" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://godbolt.org/z/3nWern4z4</a></p>
