<p>I used <code>hashbrown::HashMap</code> with its default hasher, and it is slower at <code>insert</code> but faster at <code>remove</code>. Most importantly, however, <code>update</code> is 2x faster than the <code>std</code> hash performance. This, to me, confirms that the problem lies within my NoOpHasher and how it behaves for <code>remove</code>. But I have no idea how to optimise anything here.</p>
