Task: Is this a bug in the bulletproofs crate?

 <p>The Rust <a href="https://github.com/zkcrypto/bulletproofs" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>bulletproofs</code></a> crate implements &quot;inner product argument&quot; via two functions <code>create</code> and <code>verifiy</code>. The following code tried to prove <code>&lt;[1,1, 0, 0], [0,0,1,1]&gt; = 0</code> and failed. It failed just for this case; change the vectors to, say, <code>&lt;[1,1,1,0], [0, 0, 0, 1]&gt;=0</code>, and everything works fine. I'm wondering if there is a bug in the package?</p>
<p>The <code>inner_product_proof</code> module is private. You have to download the source code locally and change a single line in <code>src/lib.rs</code> to make it public.
Line 29 <code>mod inner_product_proof;</code> is changed to <code>pub mod inner_product_proof;</code></p>
<p>Here are the config and source files: <code>Cargo.toml</code> and <code>main.rs</code>.</p>
<pre class="lang-toml prettyprint-override"><code>[package]
name = &quot;bulletproofs_test&quot;
version = &quot;0.1.0&quot;
edition = &quot;2024&quot;

[dependencies]
bulletproofs = { path = &quot;./bulletproofs&quot; }
curve25519-dalek = &quot;4.2.0&quot;
merlin = &quot;3.0.0&quot;
sha3 = &quot;0.10.8&quot;
</code></pre>
<pre><code>use std::iter;
use bulletproofs::BulletproofGens;
use bulletproofs::inner_product_proof::InnerProductProof;
use curve25519_dalek::{RistrettoPoint, Scalar};
use curve25519_dalek::traits::VartimeMultiscalarMul;
use sha3::Sha3_512;
use merlin::Transcript;

fn main() {
    ipa_test();
}


fn ipa_test() {
    // Both P and V know
    let n = 4;

    let bp_gens = BulletproofGens::new(n, 1);
    let G: Vec&lt;RistrettoPoint&gt; = bp_gens.share(0).G(n).cloned().collect();
    let H: Vec&lt;RistrettoPoint&gt; = bp_gens.share(0).G(n).cloned().collect();
    let Q = RistrettoPoint::hash_from_bytes::&lt;Sha3_512&gt;(b&quot;Q&quot;);

    // P computes and sends commitments of a and b to V
    let a = vec![
        Scalar::from(1u8),
        Scalar::from(1u8),
        Scalar::from(0u8),
        Scalar::from(0u8),
    ];
    let b: Vec&lt;Scalar&gt; = a.iter().map(|a_i| Scalar::ONE - a_i).collect();
    let c = Scalar::ZERO;

    let com_a = RistrettoPoint::vartime_multiscalar_mul(a.iter(), G.iter());
    let com_b = RistrettoPoint::vartime_multiscalar_mul(b.iter(), H.iter());

    // Now P computes the proof pi
    let mut transcript: Transcript = Transcript::new(b&quot;innerproducttest&quot;);
    let G_factors: Vec&lt;Scalar&gt; = iter::repeat(Scalar::ONE).take(n).collect();
    let H_factors: Vec&lt;Scalar&gt; = iter::repeat(Scalar::ONE).take(n).collect();

    let pi = InnerProductProof::create(
        &amp;mut transcript,
        &amp;Q,
        &amp;G_factors,
        &amp;H_factors,
        G.clone(),
        H.clone(),
        a,
        b,
    );

    // P sends com_a, com_b, c, pi to V and the latter verifies them
    let mut P = RistrettoPoint::vartime_multiscalar_mul(iter::once(c), iter::once(Q));
    P = P + com_a + com_b;


    let mut trans_verifier = Transcript::new(b&quot;innerproducttest&quot;);
    assert!(pi
        .verify(
            n,
            &amp;mut trans_verifier,
            iter::repeat(Scalar::ONE).take(n),
            iter::repeat(Scalar::ONE).take(n),
            &amp;P,
            &amp;Q,
            &amp;G,
            &amp;H
        )
        .is_ok());
}
</code></pre>


